    <li><a href="/compare/gohighlevel-vs-kajabi/">GoHighLevel vs. Kajabi: agency CRM vs. course platform</a></li>
    <li><a href="/compare/kit-vs-getresponse/">Kit vs. GetResponse: email marketing affiliate program comparison</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Alternatives by tool</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/alternatives/gohighlevel/">GoHighLevel alternatives for creators and agencies</a></li>
    <li><a href="/alternatives/systeme-io/">Systeme.io alternatives compared by use case</a></li>
    <li><a href="/alternatives/kit/">Kit alternatives compared by use case</a></li>
    <li><a href="/alternatives/getresponse/">GetResponse alternatives compared by use case</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Tools</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/tools/which-tool-fits-me/">Take the 4-question "which tool fits me?" quiz</a></li>
    <li><a href="/tools/stack-cost-calculator/">Marketing stack cost calculator: compare your own current spend to GoHighLevel's published plans</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Other tools (bounty programs)</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/brevo/">Brevo: affordable email marketing</a></li>
    <li><a href="/semrush/">Semrush for SEO</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Which of these programs pays the highest commission rate?</h3>
    <p>Systeme.io advertises the highest flat rate at 60% recurring (verified 2026-07-22). GetResponse can also reach 60% recurring, but only at its top volume tier, and that payout is capped at 12 months per referral (verified 2026-07-22) — a structural difference from Systeme.io's flat rate.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Does "60% recurring" mean the same thing for Systeme.io and GetResponse?</h3>
    <p>No. Systeme.io's 60% is a flat recurring rate paired with a 1-year attribution window (verified 2026-07-22). GetResponse's 60% is the top of a three-step tier (40% → 50% → 60%) reserved for higher-volume affiliates and is capped at 12 months per individual referral (verified 2026-07-22).</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Is GoHighLevel a good fit for a solo creator?</h3>
    <p>It can be, but GoHighLevel's core design centers on white-label, multi-client management, which is more relevant to agencies. Its commission also requires 45 days of active good-standing before a referral qualifies for payout (verified 2026-07-22), a longer qualification runway than the other three programs.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>What network do these affiliate programs run through?</h3>
    <p>GetResponse and Kit both run through PartnerStack (verified 2026-07-22). Systeme.io and GoHighLevel are vendor-direct programs.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Are Teachable, Kajabi, Brevo, and Semrush part of the same comparison?</h3>
    <p>They're adjacent tools solving different problems (course hosting, transactional email, SEO) rather than direct competitors to the four core stack tools above. They use different payout models entirely — Teachable pays 30% recurring in year one on a 30-day cookie, Kajabi is tiered up to a 100% first-month bounty, <a href="/brevo/">Brevo</a> pays a fixed bounty per paid subscription plus $5 per free-account signup on a 90-day cookie, and <a href="/semrush/">Semrush</a> pays up to $200 per sale on its SEO Toolkit plus $10 per trial on a 120-day cookie (our own Semrush link is pending an audience-threshold requirement).</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Do any of these programs guarantee affiliate earnings?</h3>
    <p>No. Commission rate, cookie window, and payout cap are contractual terms of each affiliate program, not projections or guarantees of income. Actual earnings depend on referral volume, customer retention, and program terms that can change.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
